===2000 census===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=January 31, 2008|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 265 people, 95 households, and 72 families residing in the town.  The [[population density]] was 23.0/km{{sup|2}} (59.5/mi<sup>2</sup>).  There were 118 housing units at an average density of 10.2/km{{sup|2}} (26.5/mi<sup>2</sup>).  The racial makeup of the town was 41.89% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 57.74% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 0.38% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]].  0.38% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 95 households, out of which 42.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 54.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 15.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 24.2% were non-families. 22.1% of all households were made up of individuals, and 12.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.79 and the average family size was 3.28.

In the town, the population was spread out, with 31.7% under the age of 18, 9.4% from 18 to 24, 30.2% from 25 to 44, 15.1% from 45 to 64, and 13.6% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 31 years. For every 100 females, there were 103.8 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 92.6 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $27,500, and the median income for a family was $36,250. Males had a median income of $27,708 versus $18,750 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $11,957.  About 20.7% of families and 26.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 28.6% of those under the age of eighteen and 32.5% of those 65 or over.

